@Cazen It's great to have you active in the community, as you hopefully become more active you should consider filing an Individual Contributor License Agreement  (ICLA) with Apache Software Foundation, if you haven't already. I looked a while ago and didn't see one listed for you. The ICLA would be required for a committer.

See: http://quarks.incubator.apache.org/docs/community

FYI  - your existing commits have the e-mail listed as `Cazen@korea.com` rather than the e-mail displayed for the @Cazen account, which is also different to the e-mail used to post to the list.
